com.ikala.android.bdl.tracking

Class Tracker

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ikala.android.bdl.tracking.Tracker

  • public class Tracker
extends Object
    Tracker is used track events in your app. You can use Tracker to send hits like Event, Transaction, and PageView to iKala server.

    Use getInstance(Context) to get a Tracker instance and start tracking events.
    See Also:
    getInstance(Context)

      • addEvent

        public void addEvent(EventName name,
                     Bundle params)
              throws IllegalArgumentException
        Adds an event. This event will be sent to iKala server in appropriate time.
        Parameters:
        name - the EventName
        params - the parameters of the event, only the parameters which are corresponding to the specified EventName and have the right type will be added in this event.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the EventName or Bundle is null

      • addTransaction

                           Bundle params)
                    throws IllegalArgumentException
        Adds a transaction. This transaction will be sent to iKala server in appropriate time.
        Parameters:
        name - the TransactionName
        params - the parameters of the transaction, only the parameters which are corresponding to the specified TransactionName and have the right type will be added in this transaction.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the EventName or Bundle is null

      • setCurrentPage

        public void setCurrentPage(String className,
                           String title)
                    throws IllegalArgumentException
        Sets current page. This pageview will be sent to iKala server in appropriate time. Also, the current page will be attached in the following hits like Event and Transaction.
        Parameters:
        className - the class name of current page, this is corresponding to the URL path of pageview
        title - the title of current page
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the class name is null

      • isAutoLogActivityPageEnabled

        public boolean isAutoLogActivityPageEnabled()
        Gets if the switch of activity page if auto logged.

        You can set the boolean type Android Manifest meta-data with the name com.ikala.bdl.AutoLogActivityPageEnabled to change this value. The default value is true.
        Returns:
        true if the switch of activity page is auto logged
        See Also:
        setCurrentPage(String, String)
